	<h2 class="permalink">
		<a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/2011/06/21/ncaa-football-recruit-sells-pot-brownies-until-he-gets-to-college-and-can-start-taking-bribes/">NCAA Football Recruit Sells Pot Brownies Until He Gets To College And Can Start Taking Bribes</a>
	</h2>
	
	<div class="entry">
		<p><a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/files/2011/06/Marijuana-Brownies-e1308675029480.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-5411" title="Marijuana-Brownies" src="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/files/2011/06/Marijuana-Brownies-e1308675029480.jpg" alt="" width="409" height="242" /></a>Connor Thomas, a football-player-t0-be at Montana State University, tried to make a little extra money by starting an edible marijuana distribution business at the local high school. Two major illnesses and one arrest later, it appears as if a paper route would have been the smarter decision.</p>
<p>According to court documents &#8220;Thomas faces two felony drug counts after several fellow high school graduates got sick from eating marijuana-laced brownies. Court records say two 17-year-old boys identified him as the person who made and sold the brownies for $15 on June 3.&#8221;</p>
<p>So to sum up, pot brownies apparently cost cost $15 these days.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
