<div class="post" id="post-5405">
	<div class="author">
		June 21st 12:04pm by <a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/author/sleighta/" title="Posts by Andrew Sleighter">Andrew Sleighter</a>	</div>
	
	<h2 class="permalink">
		<a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/2011/06/21/rorys-dad-poised-to-cash-in-big-on-extreme-futures-bet/">Rory&#8217;s Dad Poised To Cash In Big On Extreme Futures Bet</a>
	</h2>
	
	<div class="entry">
		<p><iframe src="http://u.tv/utvplayer/everywhere/player.aspx?vidid=137436&#038;chapid=112564&#038;arti_id=b3482382-9d01-45d8-92b2-ebd8f7b187cd&#038;clientid=100000" width="410" height="300" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>
<p>Here&#8217;s video of a 12-year-old Rory McIlroy demonstrating his golf skills. </p>
<p>Despite what you may be muttering to yourself, this IS interesting to watch when you consider that this was enough for Rory&#8217;s dad to make a <a href="http://larrybrownsports.com/golf/rory-mcilroys-dad-can-make-over-300000-if-rory-wins-british-open-by-2014/73613">100 pound bet</a> that Rory would win the British Open by 25. </p>
<p>Of course, when you make a bet like that on a kid that hasn&#8217;t hit puberty yet, you get pretty good odds&#8230; 500 to 1. </p>
<p>All in all Rory&#8217;s dad could make 200,000 pounds if Rory can win the British Open before 2014. </p>
<p>My dad tried to bet $500 that I wouldn&#8217;t win the British Open by the time I was 25, but sadly for him there were no takers. </p>
	</div>

