		<a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/2011/06/20/david-tyree-would-trade-his-catch-for-a-world-without-gay-marriage/">David Tyree Would Trade His &#8220;Catch&#8221; For A World Without Gay Marriage</a>
	</h2>
	
	<div class="entry">
		<p><a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/files/2011/06/79500728.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-5395" title="Super Bowl XLII" src="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/files/2011/06/79500728-e1308601258825.jpg" alt="" width="410" height="313" /></a>David Tyree, the wide receiver who made one of the greatest catches in Superbowl history, <a href="http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2011/06/20/david-tyree-would-trade-his-catch-to-stop-gay-marriage" target="_blank">says</a> he&#8217;d be willing to trade that catch to keep gay people from getting married to each other.</p>
<p>Earlier this week Tyree made similarly controversial comments saying that gay marriage would lead to &#8220;anarchy.&#8221;</p>
<p>I&#8217;m not one for stereotypes, but I don&#8217;t think he could have made a less interesting offer to try and buy the gay community off.</p>
