<div class="post" id="post-5382">
	<div class="author">
		June 20th 1:00pm by <a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/author/davidbreitman/" title="Posts by David Breitman">David Breitman</a>	</div>
	
	<h2 class="permalink">
		<a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/2011/06/20/marlins-offer-elderly-man-lots-of-oatmeal-money-to-help-the-franchise-relive-both-glory-years/">Marlins Offer Elderly Man Lots Of Oatmeal Money To Help The Franchise Relive Both Glory Years</a>
	</h2>
	
	<div class="entry">
		<p><a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/files/2011/06/t1_mckeon_si-e1308587844571.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-5386" title="t1_mckeon_si" src="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/files/2011/06/t1_mckeon_si-e1308587844571.jpg" alt="" width="410" height="309" /></a>After exceeding expectations by starting the year dead last in the NL East, the Florida Marlins shocked both people who still care about the Florida Marlins by bringing in 80-year-old Jack McKeon to run the team.</p>
<p>McKeon, who is apparently still alive, did help the franchise capture a World Series in 2003 and is the lone link back to a time when small market baseball had some self-esteem left.</p>
<p>The seasoned veteran hasn&#8217;t &#8220;technically&#8221; managed a team since 2005, but he has spent a lot of time yelling at neighborhood kids and wondering why they don&#8217;t make things like they used to&#8230;. so, he&#8217;s ready.</p>
<p><em>Photo: Getty Images</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
	</div>

	<div class="tags">
		Tags: <h3><a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/tag/baseball-is-relevant/" rel="tag">baseball is relevant?</a></h3>, <h3><a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/tag/jack-mckeon/" rel="tag">jack mckeon</a></h3>, <h3><a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/tag/marlins/" rel="tag">marlins</a></h3>, <h3><a href="http://sportsshow.comedycentral.com/tag/the-elderly-smell-like-death/" rel="tag">the elderly smell like death</a></h3>	</div>
	
	<div class="comments">
